  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This a randomized controlled study to test the hypothesis that patients who perform in-cast
      exercises will have superior range of motion immediately post-cast removal, without a
      concomitant increase in complication rate when compared with a control group who receives
      standard post cast care which does not include the intervention exercises.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
